## Survey of existing convection infrastructure

Per `artifacts/plan18/existing_convection_survey.txt` (60 matches in
`src/`). Key findings:

- **`AbstractConvection <: AbstractOperator`** (stub) at
  `src/Operators/AbstractOperators.jl:41`. Orphaned — no subtypes, no
  usage anywhere in src/. Plan 16b/17 did NOT use the parallel
  `AbstractDiffusion`/`AbstractSourceSink` stubs (they shipped
  `AbstractDiffusionOperator` and `AbstractSurfaceFluxOperator` with
  the `Operator` suffix). Plan 18 follows the same convention:
  `AbstractConvectionOperator` is the new type, the stub is left
  untouched.

- **ERA5 binary reader already has convection loaders**:
  `has_cmfmc`, `has_tm5conv`, `load_cmfmc_window!`, `load_tm5conv_window!`
  at `src/MetDrivers/ERA5/BinaryReader.jl:173-175, 428-483`. But
  `TransportBinaryReader` (generic, used by CATRINE production) does
  not — Commit 7.1 of plan 18 adds these.

- **`TransportBinaryDriver.supports_convection` = false** at
  `AbstractMetDriver.jl:95` (abstract default, no driver override).
  Commit 7.3 adds the override + independent capability traits
  (`supports_cmfmc`, `supports_dtrain`, `supports_tm5conv` per
  Decision 28).

- **`StructuredTransportWindow` and `FaceIndexedTransportWindow`**
  at `src/MetDrivers/TransportBinaryDriver.jl:33, 42`: 6 type
  parameters each, no convection field. Commit 2 of plan 18 adds the
  optional `convection::ConvectionForcing` field with a new type
  parameter `C`.

- **Legacy `src_legacy/Convection/`** is the port source material per
  plan 18 Decision 15 (medium cleanup for CMFMCConvection, light for
  TM5Convection). Files:
  - `ras_convection.jl` — 400 lines, GCHP-style RAS; stale "no dry
    conversion" comment at lines 41-46 is flagged for removal.
  - `tm5_matrix_convection.jl` — 625 lines, TM5 matrix scheme; spot-
    checked faithful to `tm5_conv.F90:37-191`.
  - `tiedtke_convection.jl` — not used in plan 18 (`CMFMCConvection`
    with `dtrain === nothing` fallback covers this case).

- **No plan 17-style dual-capability binaries exist yet.** All
  current production binaries are either CMFMC-only (legacy ERA5
  spectral v4) or tm5conv-only (TM5-derived). Commit 7 adds
  independent flags so a binary may carry both (Decision 28).

## Verified interface claims (plan 18 v5.1 §1.3)

Re-verified against current tree at baseline commit 126dbdc (all
match the v5.1 table; claims remain valid):

- `CellState{Basis, A, Raw, Names}` at `src/State/CellState.jl:42-46`
- `AbstractMassBasis`, `DryBasis`, `MoistBasis` at `src/State/Basis.jl:10-24`
- `AbstractTransportWindow{Basis}` at `src/MetDrivers/TransportBinaryDriver.jl:18`
- `StructuredTransportWindow{Basis, M, PS, F, Q, D}` 6-param at `:33`
- `FaceIndexedTransportWindow{Basis, M, PS, F, Q, D}` 6-param at `:42`
- `AtmosGrid{H <: AbstractHorizontalMesh, ...}` at `src/Grids/AbstractMeshes.jl:111`
- No `AbstractFaceIndexedMesh` type (face-indexed dispatch goes
  through `Raw <: AbstractArray{_,3}` per Decision 25)
- `DrivenSimulation` has `model`, `driver`, `window`, `time`,
  `iteration`, `current_window_index` — verified by the A3 fix +
  `test_current_time.jl`
- `TransportBinaryDriver` struct holds only `reader` + `grid`
  (stateless) — confirmed at A3 time.

